<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Corporal1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Corporal,</orth> subst., the lowest officer of the infantry: <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 128</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 2, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.166" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.244" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 244</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 1</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 1</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 1</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 1</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 3</bibl>. <emph>and I to be a c. of his</emph> (Cupid's) <cit><quote>field,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 3.189" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 189</bibl></cit> (== his adjutant).
